It's the first energy drink themed after an automotive product; it's one of the
OG energy drinks, having launched in 2004. It is currently owned by Monster
Beverage but was formerly a Coke product. It changed hands in 2015 from Coke to
Monster; it was originally created by Fuze who sold it to Coke in 2007, a fact
I've mentioned [[before|Living_In_The_Energy_Drink_Renaissance]] on this
website.

This is their zero sugar alternative to full-sugar NOS. As I understand there
was a different formula for a similar zero-sugar NOS prior to this[^1] which
came in a white can. In addition there was NOS Zero[^2] in a gray can. Both of
these have been discontinued. The current iteration of NOS sugar-free comes in a
can with the same colorway as the full-sugar NOS but it just says “ZERO” above
the name “NOS”.

